Spring.Container.Common Namespace

Summary

Represents namespace Spring.Container.Common.

Classes
 NameDescription
ImplementsAttribute

Applies this attribute to tell the IoC container which service is implemented by the target component. In addition, a service name can be specified.

InjectAttribute

Applies the InjectAttribute to injectable instance members of a class. e.g. constructors, methods, properties and even fields. Also works on parameters of a method.

LifetimeAttributeBase

Represents an abstract lifetime attribute class base.

PooledAttribute

Represents that the target component can be pooled.

SingletonAttribute

Applies this attribute when a component shares the single instance.

SingletonAttributeBase

Represents type SingletonAttributeBase.

SingletonPerThreadAttribute

Applies this attribute when a component shares the single instance per thread.

TransientAttribute

Represents that a new instance of the component will be created when requested.

IInitializable

Lifecycle interface. If a component implements this interface, the dependency injection container will invoke the Initialize method when initiating an instance of the component.

IRecyclable

Lifecycle interface. Only called for components that belongs to a pool when the component comes back to the pool.

IRefCounted

Lifecycle interface. Implement this interface on a class that does not inherit from TInterfacedObject to make it compatible with pooling.

IRegistration

Represents type IRegistration.

IStartable

Lifecycle interface. Represents that the component can be started and stopped.
